A manhunt has been launched after a mum and her seven-year-old daughter were sexually assaulted on their way home from school. They were followed by a man who tried to touch them both inappropriately in an alleyway in the Stoke area of Coventry at around 3.30pm on Tuesday. Both were able to get to safety before calling the police, according to Coventry Live. West Midlands Police said in a statement: ‘We’re investigating a sexual assault which happened around 3.30pm on Tuesday (July 5) on Knight Avenue in Coventry. ‘A mother and her seven-year-old daughter were followed by man who attempted to inappropriately touch them. ‘Anyone with information is urged to contact us via Live Chat on our website quoting 20/617960/22.’ Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at webnews@metro.co.uk. For more stories like this, check our news page.